THERE are
724 201 confirmed cases of the coronavirus worldwide and 34 026 deaths in 177
countries. South
Africa has conducted 35 593 tests and 1280 people tested positive for the virus
while there have been 2 deaths reported so far. The country
has been in lockdown since Thursday midnight after President Cyril Ramaphosa
announced the lockdown in order to curb the spread of the virus. South
Africans are known for making tough situations lite with laughter, they took to
social media and began sharing what they have been up to while in lockdown.              